The paper investigates the impact of class selectivity on the performance of deep neural networks (DNNs), which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments are conducted on convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the interpretation of individual neurons in DNNs, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
